<Link id="l00279" /><CodeLine lineNumber="279"><Highlight kind="comment">/// A closure is a set of virtual register representing all of the edges in</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00280" /><CodeLine lineNumber="280"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the closure, as well as all of the instructions connected by those edges.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00281" /><CodeLine lineNumber="281"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00282" /><CodeLine lineNumber="282"><Highlight kind="comment">/// A closure may encompass virtual registers in the same register bank that</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00283" /><CodeLine lineNumber="283"><Highlight kind="comment">/// have different widths. For example, it may contain 32-bit GPRs as well as</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00284" /><CodeLine lineNumber="284"><Highlight kind="comment">/// 64-bit GPRs.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00285" /><CodeLine lineNumber="285"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00286" /><CodeLine lineNumber="286"><Highlight kind="comment">/// A closure that computes an address (i.e. defines a virtual register that is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00287" /><CodeLine lineNumber="287"><Highlight kind="comment">/// used in a memory operand) excludes the instructions that contain memory</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00288" /><CodeLine lineNumber="288"><Highlight kind="comment">/// operands using the address. Such an instruction will be included in a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00289" /><CodeLine lineNumber="289"><Highlight kind="comment">/// different closure that manipulates the loaded or stored value.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
